  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">The photoassociation of Efimov trimer, composed of three identical bosons, is studied utilizing the multipole expansion. For identical particles the leading contribution comes from the r^2 s-mode operator and from the quadrupole d-mode operator. Log-periodic oscillations are found in the photoassociation response function, both near the energy threshold for the leading s-wave reaction, and in the high frequency tail for all partial waves.</subfield>
    <subfield code="9">arXiv</subfield>
  </datafield>
